# Run unit tests before pushing to origin

Project hooks run on `beforeShellExecution` when a `git push` targets `origin` (see [Cursor Hooks](https://cursor.com/docs/hooks) and `.cursor/hooks.json`). The hook runs the full frontend and backend test suites before the push is allowed.

## Commands

- **Frontend (JavaScript / Vue / Vite)**: use `npm run test:run` for a one-shot CI-style run. In `package.json`, `npm run test` starts Vitest in **watch** mode, which is poor for automation and will not exit; prefer `npm run test:run` when validating changes.
- **Backend (PHP / Laravel)**: use `sail test`. Other PHP commands stay on Sail per **Use Sail for PHP**.

## Agent workflow expectations

- Run the relevant test command(s) before finishing work on frontend or backend changes so failures are caught early.
- Before `git push` to `origin`, expect the hook to run both suites when `package.json` and Sail are present.
- If the hook denies a push, read the denial message, fix tests or code, re-run the same commands locally, then retry the push.
